1507685-a.folder: Eighth Avenue - 124th Street - 125th Street, west side, Manhattan, NY
1507685-a.title: Eighth Avenue - 124th Street - 125th Street, west side

465673-a.title: The Bellehaven, 515 West 124th Street;  Plan of first floor; Plan of upper floors.

710255f-a.text:
Eighth Avenue, east side, north from W. 124th to 125th Street, showing a new tax-payer at this frontage occupying a lot 200x100 and upon which formerly stood various 4 and 5 story structures. These consisted of buildings that bore No's. 272 to 280 W. 125th Street; No's 2310 to 2322 Eighth Avenue; and 271 W. 124th Street. Note the Ninth Avenue "El" on this thoroughfare and its 125th St. station.
P.L. Sperr
March 19, 1936

715324f-a.text:
W. 124th Street, west from eighth avenue as viewed from the Ninth Avenue Elevated Line platform at that point. Note at St. Nicholas Avenue the Municipal (Ninth Avenue) Subway under construction. In the far distance appears Grants Tomb and the International
Home.
September 1927.
Geo. L. Balgue
